# Web Audio Node Editor Websurf Rules

## Project Structure
- `/app`: Next.js application routing and pages
- `/components`: React components organized by function
- `/lib`: Utility functions and tools
- `/public`: Static assets like images and SVGs
- `/styles`: Global CSS styles

## Core Components
- `AudioNodeProvider`: Context provider for audio node management and connections
- `NodeEditor`: Main canvas where nodes are placed and connected
- `ControlPanel`: Parameter controls for selected nodes
- `Sidebar`: Node selection and application controls

## Key Concepts
- Audio nodes (source, destination, effects) are connected to create processing chains
- Nodes have inputs, outputs, and adjustable parameters
- Connections between nodes are visualized with SVG paths
- Context menu allows adding nodes and other operations

## Development Notes
- UI components use shadcn/ui design system based on Radix UI
- Dark/light mode supported via CSS variables
- Node parameters automatically update based on node type
- Drag and drop functionality for node placement
- Right-click context menu support

## Common Tasks
- Add new node types in the AudioNodeProvider
- Update parameter controls in ControlPanel component
- Modify node visualization in AudioNodeComponent
- Change connection styling in NodeEditor component